只好；必须得；表示客观上不得不做某事

必须；不得不；被迫；必然要；不可避免（劝告或建议时用；表示一定真实或肯定发生）

1.en: He had a secret which he was not ready to tell, yet, but if this mutinous depression was not broken up soon, he would have to bring it out.
1.cn: 他有一个秘密，不打算马上说出来，但眼下这股消沉的士气必须扭转，他不得不亮出这张王牌了。

2.en: "We really don't have to be quite as fastidious unless the child has an immune deficiency, " she said.
2.cn: 她说：“除非宝宝存在免疫缺陷，否则我们真的没有必要过于认真。”

3.en: But if the economy continued to deteriorate and the industry continued to deteriorate, then even Ford might have to need a bridge loan also.
3.cn: 但如果经济继续恶化，行业形势每况愈下，那么即便是福特汽车可能也不得不需要过渡性贷款。

0.en: We have to assume everyone aboard those carriers is Hydra.
0.cn: 我们不得不假设那上面都是九头蛇的人。

1.en: I have to say, you sure can ride.
1.cn: 我不得不说，你的骑车技术很厉害。

2.en: Oh, honey, you are pretty. No, you have to say that.
2.cn: 亲爱的，你很漂亮。你是不得不这么说。

3.en: I have to, baby, daddy has to. Ice them. No, no, no!
3.cn: 我不得不这么做，宝贝，爸爸也无奈，做掉他们。不，不，不！

4.en: It is too foggy to find the playground. So Peppa and George have to go back home.
4.cn: 雾太大了找不到运动场。所以佩佩和乔治不得不返回家。

5.en: How's that broccoli? It's gross but I have to eat it because I met somebody.
5.cn: 西兰花味道怎么样？难吃又不得不吃，因为我有对象了。

6.en: We have to fight Congress for every dollar in our budget, each year.
6.cn: 我们不得不跟国会争夺我们预算里的每一分钱，年年如此。

7.en: Okay, so, basically, you're the reason I have to walk up and down three flights of stairs every day?
7.cn: 所以你就是害我不得不每天上上下下跑三层楼梯的人。

8.en: We're gonna make this tank so filthy the dentist will have to clean it. Good work!
8.cn: 我们要搞的这个水箱脏到那个牙医不得不清理的地步。干得好!

9.en: I'm going to make your face so hot that Old Nick will have to take you to the hospital, in his truck.
9.cn: 我要把你的脸弄得很烫，这样老尼克就不得不开着卡车送你去医院。

10.en: Where are we going to get trees from? We have to drive big trucks around the world and look for trees.
10.cn: 我们从哪里能弄到树呢？我们不得不开着大卡车，在满世界寻找树了。

11.en: Now look, as long as we continue to increase the population, we're going to have to continue to grow and eat genetically modified foods, and that's the only position that I'll take today.
11.cn: 随着人口不断增长，我们会不得不使用转基因产品，这是我的唯一立场。

12.en: Can't figure out what to do? I remember those days. Now, if you'll excuse me, I have to stay right here.
12.cn: 不知道该怎么办吗？我也有过这种日子，而现在，请原谅我不得不，继续留在这。

13.en: I came to New York specifically to do this play. My play. And now, because of you, I have to go to Hanukkah dinner at my parents' house.
13.cn: 我跑到纽约来就是为了这部戏。是我的戏，可现在就因为你我不得不去我爸妈家参加光明节晚餐。

14.en: I understand your reticence, Dr. Cooper, and I sympathize, but the hard facts are, occasionally, we have to shake a few hands and kiss a few butts to raise money for our research.
14.cn: 你不情愿我很理解，库珀博士，我深表同情，但残酷的事实摆在面前，有时候我们不得不为了募集研究资金而跟某些人溜须拍马。

15.en: So you betrayed me? No! It wasn't a betrayal. It was more of a "I can't afford any more points on my license." I already have to buy my insurance from this place in the Cayman Islands.
15.cn: 于是你就把我出卖了？才没有，这哪是出卖。我只不过表示“我的驾照已经没分好扣了”，我已经不得不去开曼群岛上买车险了。

16.en: Look, Phil, I want to figure this out, but right now, I have to get to Chavez Ridge and cover this wind event. You know what? We're not friends. Go. Get... Phil? You're being ridiculous.
16.cn: 菲尔，我也想把话说清楚，但现在我不得不赶去查韦斯岭报道这次强风事件。让我告诉你，我们友尽了。你走。你出去……菲尔？你太荒唐了。

17.en: I have to say I'm a little nervous. You should be.
17.cn: 不得不说还真是有点紧张啊。应该的。

18.en: I have to say, I'm finding your bedside manner a little lacking.
18.cn: 我不得不说，我觉得你对病人的态度不够耐心。
